overview: The user initiated a review of their sleep questionnaire application,
  providing a detailed specification. The assistant performed a thorough
  analysis, identifying both well-implemented features and several critical
  gaps, such as the absence of a tiredness severity scale, COMISA detection, and
  insufficient sleep syndrome logic. Following this review, the assistant began
  implementing the identified high-priority items. This included updating the
  application's types, validation schemas, UI components, and report generation
  logic to incorporate a 1-10 tiredness severity scale with safety warnings,
  detect and report COMISA, and identify insufficient sleep syndrome based on
  specific criteria. The implementation involved modifications across various
  frontend and backend files to ensure comprehensive integration of these new
  features.
